Maximum horizon height around a station

Source: R/compute_horizon_max.R
compute_horizon_max.Rd

Compute maximum horizon height in degrees from a station location in UTM 33 and based on three DEMs: Digital Terrain Model, Digital Surface Model and 20km-Digital Terrain Model

compute_horizon_max(
  stn = NULL,
  step = 10,
  f_plot_polygon = FALSE,
  f_output_all = FALSE
)

Arguments

stn

A SpatVector with station attributes from "get_latlon_frost"

step

An interval in degrees at which the horizon will be computed, default is every 10 deg.

f_plot_polygon

A boolean setting boundary values to -20 deg to facilitate plotting as polygon

f_output_all

A boolean to export all horizons: dem, dsm, demkm & max

Value

A dataframe with `horizon_height` in degrees and `azimuth` angle in degrees at which the horizon is computed in degrees
